label.value: adult usnea subesophageal neuron

value.value: Adult local neuron with its soma in the lateral gnathal ganglion (Sterne et al., 2021). It has both dendritic and axonal arborization in the gnathal ganglion, with biased synapse distribution within this region (Sterne et al., 2021). It is bilateral, but most of its innervation is in the ipsilateral hemisphere (Sterne et al., 2021). It receives a large amount of input from gustatory neurons, mainly water- and sugar-sensing neurons, and responds to water stimulus (Shiu et al., 2022). Its activation results in proboscis extension (Shiu et al., 2022). It is predicted to be GABAergic (Shiu et al., 2022).

definition.value: Neurotransmitter prediction based on machine learning classification (Shiu et al., 2022).

label.value: adult vice subesophageal neuron

value.value: Adult interneuron with its soma in the subesophageal zone (Sterne et al., 2021). It has axonal arborization in the gnathal ganglion and both dendritic and axonal arborization in the vest (Sterne et al., 2021). It is ipsilateral (Sterne et al., 2021).

label.value: adult vixen subesophageal neuron

value.value: Adult local neuron with its soma in the lateral subesophageal zone (Sterne et al., 2021). It has both dendritic and axonal arborization in the gnathal ganglion, with mixed synapse distribution within this region (Sterne et al., 2021). It is bilateral, with similar innervation in each hemisphere (Sterne et al., 2021).

label.value: adult wafflecone subesophageal neuron

value.value: Adult local neuron with its soma in the lateral subesophageal zone (Sterne et al., 2021). It has both dendritic and axonal arborization in the gnathal ganglion, with mixed synapse distribution within this region (Sterne et al., 2021). It is mainly ipsilateral, but arborizes close to the midline (Sterne et al., 2021).

label.value: adult weaver subesophageal neuron

value.value: Adult projection neuron with its soma in the lateral subesophageal zone (Sterne et al., 2021). It has dendritic arborization in the inferior posterior slope and cantle, axonal arborization in the inferior clamp and posterior lateral protocerebrum and both dendritic and axonal arborization in the superior posterior slope (Sterne et al., 2021). It is bilateral (Sterne et al., 2021).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg74

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma in the ventral gnathal ganglion (Sterne et al., 2021). In the brain, it has bilateral dendritic and axonal arborization in the gnathal ganglion (Sterne et al., 2021). It descends on the contralateral side of the cervical connective, follows the dorsal lateral tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus, and has axonal arborization in the T1, T2 and T3 leg neuropils, and the abdominal neuromere (Sterne et al., 2021; Sturner et al., 2024). There are approximately four of these cells per organism (Sturner et al., 2024).

label.value: adult whisker subesophageal neuron

value.value: Adult local neuron with its soma in the ventral gnathal ganglion (Sterne et al., 2021). It has both dendritic and axonal arborization in the gnathal ganglion, with biased synapse distribution within this region (Sterne et al., 2021). It is bilateral, with most of its innervation in the contralateral hemisphere (Sterne et al., 2021).

label.value: efferent neuron

value.value: Neuron that transmits information out of the central nervous system (CNS). It has its soma in the cell body rind of the CNS, a dendrite in the CNS and an axon projecting through a nerve (Prokop, 2006).

label.value: adult efferent neuron

value.value: Any efferent neuron of the adult.

label.value: larval efferent neuron

value.value: Any efferent neuron of the larva.

label.value: haltere muscle motor neuron

value.value: Motor neuron that innervates a muscle of the haltere. It receives input in the haltere neuropil and fasciculates with the haltere (dorsal metathoracic) nerve (Phelps et al., 2021).

label.value: neck muscle motor neuron of VNC

value.value: Motor neuron of the ventral nerve cord that innervates a muscle of the neck (Phelps et al., 2021; Cheong et al., 2024). It has its soma in the prothoracic neuromere and receives input in the neck neuropil (Phelps et al., 2021).

definition.value: Cheong et al. (2024) note that some neck muscle motor neurons have somas in the brain.

label.value: labellar mechanosensory bristle

value.value: Bristle on the outer surface of the labellum that is solely mechanosensory (Shanbhag et al., 2001). There are two of these on each side and they are found in a lateral position (Shanbhag et al., 2001).

label.value: short labellar taste bristle S-c

value.value: Short labellar taste bristle that does not respond to bitter stimuli (Weiss et al., 2011) and does not contain a Gr66a-expressing bitter-sensitive neuron (Weiss et al., 2011; Jaeger et al., 2018).

definition.value: Existence, identity and nomenclature of particular sensilla may not correspond between studies.

label.value: sour-sensing neuron of the leg

value.value: Sensory neuron that responds to sour (acidic) stimuli and innervates a taste bristle in the leg. These are characterized by expression of ionotropic receptors Ir76b and Ir25a, which are required for their response to acids, and the absence of sweet (Gr64f) and bitter (Gr33a) gustatory receptors (Chen and Amrein, 2017).

definition.value: Sweet (Gr64f) and bitter (Gr33a) neurons of the leg do not respond to sour stimuli (Chen and Amrein, 2017).

label.value: sour-sensing neuron of mesothoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5b

value.value: Sensory neuron that has a dendrite in the mesothoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5b and is capable of detecting sour stimuli (Chen and Amrein, 2017). It responds to a range of carboxylic and mineral acids (Chen and Amrein, 2017). There is one of these per 5b bristle (Chen and Amrein, 2017).

label.value: sour-sensing neuron of mesothoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5v

value.value: Sensory neuron that has a dendrite in the mesothoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5v and is capable of detecting sour stimuli (Chen and Amrein, 2017). It responds specifically to glycolic and malic acids and also responds to high concentrations of salt (Chen and Amrein, 2017). There are two of these per 5v bristle (Chen and Amrein, 2017).

label.value: sour-sensing neuron of metathoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5b

value.value: Sensory neuron that has a dendrite in the metathoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5b and is capable of detecting sour stimuli (Chen and Amrein, 2017). It responds to a range of carboxylic and mineral acids (Chen and Amrein, 2017). There is one of these per 5b bristle (Chen and Amrein, 2017).

label.value: sour-sensing neuron of metathoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5v

value.value: Sensory neuron that has a dendrite in the metathoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5v and is capable of detecting sour stimuli (Chen and Amrein, 2017). It responds specifically to glycolic and malic acids and also responds to high concentrations of salt (Chen and Amrein, 2017). There are two of these per 5v bristle (Chen and Amrein, 2017).

label.value: sour-sensing neuron of prothoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5b

value.value: Sensory neuron that has a dendrite in the prothoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5b and is capable of detecting sour stimuli (Chen and Amrein, 2017). It responds to a range of carboxylic and mineral acids (Chen and Amrein, 2017). There is one of these per 5b bristle (Chen and Amrein, 2017).

label.value: sour-sensing neuron of prothoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5s

value.value: Sensory neuron that has a dendrite in the prothoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5s and is capable of detecting sour stimuli (Chen and Amrein, 2017). It responds to a range of carboxylic and mineral acids (Chen and Amrein, 2017). There is one of these per 5s bristle (Chen and Amrein, 2017).

label.value: sour-sensing neuron of prothoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5v

value.value: Sensory neuron that has a dendrite in the prothoracic leg tarsal taste bristle 5v and is capable of detecting sour stimuli (Chen and Amrein, 2017). It responds specifically to glycolic and malic acids and also responds to high concentrations of salt (Chen and Amrein, 2017). There are two of these per 5v bristle (Chen and Amrein, 2017).

label.value: labellar taste bristle chemosensory neuron

value.value: Chemosensory neuron that innervates a labial taste bristle. There are 2-4 of these innervating each bristle (Shanbhag et al., 2001).

label.value: costal wing margin

value.value: Region of the anterior wing margin found along the length of the costal vein (Palka et al., 1979). It harbors sensilla whose axons travel via the costal nerve (Palka et al., 1979).

label.value: costal wing bristle

value.value: Any chaeta (FBbt:00005177) that is part of some costal wing margin (FBbt:00051979).

label.value: tegula wing bristle

value.value: Any chaeta (FBbt:00005177) that is part of some tegula (FBbt:00004730).

label.value: cell body rind of adult posterior prothoracic neuromere

value.value: Posterior region of the adult prothoracic neuromere cell body rind, found close to the root of the prothoracic leg nerve.

label.value: cell body rind of adult posterior mesothoracic neuromere

value.value: Posterior region of the adult mesothoracic neuromere cell body rind, found close to the root of the mesothoracic leg nerve.

label.value: cell body rind of adult posterior metathoracic neuromere

value.value: Posterior region of the adult metathoracic neuromere cell body rind, found close to the root of the metathoracic leg nerve.

label.value: larval ring gland projection neuron

value.value: Larval neuron that has its soma in the central nervous system and projects through the nervus corporis cardiaci (Huckesfeld et al., 2021). It releases neuropeptide in the ring gland or aorta via non-synaptic dense core vesicles (Huckesfeld et al., 2021).

label.value: dorsal organ warming cell

value.value: Ir68a, Ir25a and Ir93a -expressing neuron of the dorsal organ ganglion (DOG), activated by temperature increases (Hernandez-Nunez et al., 2021). All three of these Ir genes are necessary for heating-induced activity of these cells, with Ir68a specifying warming, rather than cooling sensitivity (Hernandez-Nunez et al., 2021). Two of these cells are found in each DOG and each projects to a different antennal lobe glomerulus, distinct from the one targeted by the cool cells, in the posterior dorsal antennal lobe (Hernandez-Nunez et al., 2021). The sensory dendrites of these neurons do not exhibit the membrane infoldings seen in the cool cells and they extend a thin dendrite into the central dome sensillum (Hernandez-Nunez et al., 2021).

value.value: Region of the larval ventral nerve cord cell body rind that overlies the neuropil of the prothoracic neuromere.

label.value: adult antennal sensillum

value.value: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some antenna (FBbt:00004511).

label.value: empty antennal sensillum

value.value: Hair structure of the antenna that resembles a sensillum, but lacks sensory neurons (Gonzales et al., 2021). Auxiliary cells (tormogen, trichogen, thecogen) may or may not still be present (Gonzales et al., 2021).

definition.value: Biological significance of these is unclear, but speculated to be due to neuronal turnover (Gonzales et al., 2021).

label.value: antennal basiconic sensillum abx(3)

value.value: Large olfactory basiconic sensillum of the antenna that houses the dendrites of three olfactory receptor neurons (Gonzales et al., 2021).

definition.value: Neuron Or/Ir expression not determined by Gonzales et al. (2021).

label.value: antennal basiconic sensillum abx(1)

value.value: Small antennal basiconic sensillum innervated by the dendrite of a single olfactory receptor neuron (Gonzales et al., 2021).

label.value: larval corazonin neuron

value.value: Any larval neuron (FBbt:00001446) that is capable of some peptide hormone secretion (GO:0030072) and expresses Crz (FBgn0013767).

label.value: larval corazonin neuron of pars lateralis

value.value: Larval corazonin-expressing neuron that has its soma in the pars lateralis (Siegmund and Korge, 2001). It projects to the ring gland, via the nervus corporis cardiaci, where it has peptide release sites in the aorta, corpus cardiacum, corpus allatum and the prothoracic gland (Siegmund and Korge, 2001; Imura et al., 2020; Huckesfeld et al., 2021; Reinhard et al., 2023). In the prothoracic gland, it makes contacts with the PTTH neurons, which express the corazonin receptor (Imura et al., 2020). There are three of these cells per hemisphere (Siegmund and Korge, 2001; Park et al., 2008; Imura et al., 2020). It also expresses short neuropeptide F (Park et al., 2008).
